name: Nike Air Zoom GT Hustle 2 Greater Than Ever
story: The Nike GT Hustle 2 ‘Greater Than Ever’ delivers a performance basketball shoe that takes design cues from the running shoe space. The minimalist upper is crafted from breathable black mesh with tonal iridescent overlays and a padded mid-cut collar. Accented with a crimson topline and treated to a purple iridescent finish, a lightweight Phylon midsole features full-length Zoom Air cushioning for on-court responsiveness. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole provides multi-directional traction.

name: Zoom Kobe 4 Protro 'Girl Dad'
story: The Nike Zoom Kobe 4 Protro ‘Girl Dad’ is a nod to the bond that Kobe Bryant shared with his daughters. A muted teal suede upper built with rolled edges is contrasted with black accents on the Swoosh, collar lining and interior tongue. A chrome-plated heel counter displays Kobe Bryant’s signature on the lateral side, while the inside tongue showcases a ‘Girl Dad’ inscription. The sneaker rides on a lightweight Phylon midsole with a springy Zoom Air unit in the heel. Underfoot, a herringbone-traction rubber outsole reveals a carbon fiber shank plate for midfoot support.

name: Kobe 8 Protro 'Mambacita'
story: The Nike Kobe 8 Protro ‘Mambacita’ pays homage to Gigi Bryant, featuring an all-over butterfly print across an upper built with off-white Engineered Mesh. An embroidered gold Swoosh adorns the lateral side, while the back heel is marked with ‘Gigi’ on the left shoe and her jersey number on the right. Performance benefits include a drop-in React foam midsole and a carbon fiber shank plate. A herringbone-traction rubber outsole provides optimal grip.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Premium Pastoral Print
story: The Nike Dunk Low Premium SB ‘Pastoral Print’ dons a grey canvas upper covered in bucolic graphics depicting fluffy clouds, soaring birds and leafy trees. Brown piping outlines the Swoosh, eyestay, and forefoot and heel overlay. A tan Nike SB tag adorns the stuffed tongue, while a Nike wordmark is embroidered in bronze lettering on the back tab. A solid off-white finish is applied to the rubber cupsole, featuring stitched sidewall construction and an outsole equipped with a hardwood-ready pivot circle.

name: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Venice Beach (2024)
story: The Nike Kobe 8 Protro ‘Venice Beach’ celebrates the vibrant culture of the Southern California city. Splashes of red, teal and yellow enliven a seamless upper built with grey Engineered Mesh. Additional pops of color arrive via a turquoise external heel counter and an orange textile collar lining. In terms of performance, the low-top is equipped with a drop-in React foam midsole and a carbon fiber shank plate. A semi-translucent rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for superior grip.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low Navy Gum
Nike Air More Uptempo 96 Black Star Blue
Air Max 1 '86 OG Golf 'Big Bubble - Royal'
story: The Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 OG Golf ‘Big Bubble’ presents a course-ready version of the original ‘Royal’ AM1. The water-resistant upper features white mesh construction with synthetic suede overlays in a pale grey finish. Contrasting blue accents land on the signature Swoosh, suede mudguard, and the embroidered Nike Air branding that adorns the back heel. The white foam midsole packs a large-volume Max Air unit inspired by the Air Max 1 that initially released in 1986. Underfoot, the rubber outsole utilizes an integrated traction pattern for optimal grip.

name: Wmns Air Max 1 '86 OG 'Big Bubble - Royal'
story: The Nike Women’s Air Max 1 ‘86 OG ‘Big Bubble’ in ‘Royal’ features an original color scheme, paired with revised tooling inspired by the short-lived introductory run of the vintage running shoe. The upper combines ventilated white mesh with synthetic suede overlays in a pale grey finish. Royal blue accents settle on the molded eyelets, Swoosh, and suede mudguard. The sneaker rests on a white foam midsole, rendered in a classic wedge shape and fitted with a large-window Max Air unit in the heel.

name: Nike Air Max DN Voltage Purple (2024)
Dunk Low 'Summit White Light Smoke Grey'
Wmns Sabrina 1 'Oregon Ducks'
story: The Nike Women’s Sabrina 1 ‘Oregon Ducks’ pays homage to Sabrina Ionescu’s alma mater. The shoe makes use of a mesh and textile upper in contrasting green and yellow hues. Sabrina’s personal logo appears on the tongue patch, while a Swoosh outlined in black embroidery adorns the lateral side panel. ‘QUACK’ is inscribed on the lateral sidewall in a playful nod to the Oregon Ducks. Performance benefits include a cushy React foam midsole with a top-loaded Zoom Air unit in the forefoot.

name: Nike Jordan Air Ship PE SP Rust Pink
story: The Jordan Air Ship PE SP ‘Rust Pink’ delivers an off-white leather upper contrasted by muted pink accents on the forefoot overlay, Swoosh, and collar. The latter is branded with an embroidered Nike wordmark on the lateral side. The sneaker rides atop a rubber cupsole, built with sidewall construction and an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel. The pink rubber outsole features the same traction pattern used on the Air Jordan 1.

name: Nike Dunk Low LX Year of the Dragon (2024) (Women's)
Wmns Air Max 90 Futura 'Give Her Flowers'
Wmns Air Max 1 '87 'Malachite'
story: The Nike Women’s Air Max 1 ‘87 ‘Malachite’ features an upper that combines breathable white mesh with grey synthetic suede overlays at the midfoot and heel. The latter displays Nike Air branding in green embroidery, matching the molded upper eyelets, signature Swoosh and suede mudguard. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a white polyurethane midsole, featuring a visible Air-sole unit in the heel.

name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Be True To Her School LSU (Women's)
Blazer Mid '77 'Waffle'
story: The Nike Blazer Mid ‘77 ‘Waffle’ features an off-white leather upper with tonal hairy suede overlays. The retro design is updated with an embossed waffle texture on the tan suede Swoosh. The diamond-shaped pattern makes repeat appearances on the Nike tongue tag and suede back tab, marked with embroidered Nike branding. The sneaker rests on a white vulcanized rubber midsole, supported by a herringbone-traction outsole in gum rubber.

Wmns Dunk Low LX 'Ale Brown Ostrich'
story: The Nike Women’s Dunk Low LX ‘Ale Brown Ostrich’ makes use of a leather upper, featuring a white base with glossy brown overlays in a luxe ostrich texture. Atop the tongue, a leather tag displays a standard Nike logo in metallic gold lettering. Heritage details include a padded low-cut collar and perforated detailing on the toe box. The sneaker rides on a standard white midsole, reinforced underfoot by a gum rubber outsole.

name: Nike Dunk Low LX Gorge Green Ostrich (Women's)
story: The Nike Women’s Dunk Low LX ‘Gorge Green Ostrich’ showcases a crisp white leather base, contrasted by ostrich-textured overlays in a glossy green finish. Nike branding is stamped in metallic gold lettering on the tongue tag, while a Nike wordmark is debossed on the back tab. The low-top sits on a durable rubber cupsole, featuring white sidewalls and a grippy gum rubber outsole.

colorway: Stadium Green/Hyper Violet/Barely Green/Playful Pink/University Gold/Lightening
name: KD 16 'All-Star'
story: The Nike KD 16 ‘All-Star’ delivers green tiger stripes on the breathable mesh upper, contrasted by a pink synthetic leather overlay and a translucent TPU support wing in University Gold. The latter reveals Kevin Durant’s ‘Easy Money’ branding on the lateral side, while a holographic ‘KD’ tongue patch continues the currency theme. The cushioning setup comprises a lightweight foam midsole with a Zoom strobel unit in the heel and a bottom-loaded Zoom Air unit in the forefoot.

name: Ja 1 'All-Star'
story: The Nike Ja 1 ‘All-Star’ sports a breathable mesh upper in black and Bright Crimson. A tonal synthetic leather overlay reinforces the forefoot, while a TPU Swoosh in Bright Mandarin wraps around the heel. The low-top rides on a lightweight Phylon midsole with springy Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot. The blue translucent rubber outsole reveals Ja Morant’s quote upon signing with Nike: ‘Now I’m proud to say I work for the check.’

name: Air Max Plus Drift 'Phantom Cacao Wow'
Nike Cortez SE Valentine's Day (2024) (Women's)
story: The Nike Women’s Cortez ‘Valentine’s Day’ delivers a two-tone colorway of the vintage running shoe in honor of February 14. Built with off-white leather, the upper features red suede detailing on the signature Swoosh and back tab. The latter displays a pink heart with embossed Swoosh branding. Additional nods to the romantic holiday include heart-shaped lace dubrae and a Nike tongue tag marked with a pair of heart-shaped cherries. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length foam midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

name: Nike SB Dunk Low City Of Love Light Bone
story: Representing one-half of the ‘City of Love Collection,’ the Nike Dunk Low Premium SB ‘Light Bone’ blends luxe materials with a tonal design. The upper features a white satin base with ivory suede overlays at the forefoot and heel. A tumbled leather Swoosh maintains the monochrome color palette. In a nod to the mythic red thread of fate, graphic insoles display two hands linked by red string tied around the pinky finger. The theme is repeated with red stitching encircling the off-white rubber midsole.

colorway: Burgundy Crush/Dark Team Red/Earth/Dark Pony/University Red/Earth
name: Nike SB Dunk Low City Of Love Burgundy Crush
story: Launching as part of the ‘City of Love Collection,’ the Nike Dunk Low Premium SB ‘Burgundy Crush’ gives the retro silhouette a monochrome makeover. Rich burgundy tones are applied to an upper built with leather and textured nubuck. Glossy trim outlines a crackled leather Swoosh in a tonal finish. Inside the shoe, custom insoles reference the mythic red thread of fate, displaying two hands linked by red string tied around the pinky finger. The low-top is mounted on a rubber cupsole, rendered in a matching burgundy hue and accented with speckled detailing.

name: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 SE PRM Valentine's Day (2024) (Women's)

colorway: University Red/Burgundy Crush-Gym Red-Team Red-Pacific Moss
name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Layers of Love
story: The Nike Air Force 1 Low ‘Layers of Love’ dresses the iconic hoops shoe in a suede upper in complementary crimson and maroon hues. Heritage details include a variable width lacing system and a perforated toe box. Nike Air branding adorns the woven tongue tag and burgundy suede back tab, contrasted by a heel strip in olive green. The low-top is mounted on a rubber cupsole, rendered in a dark burgundy finish and fitted with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning.

name: Air Max Penny 1 'Penny Story'
story: The Nike Air Max Penny 1 ‘Penny Story’ takes inspiration from a 1997 Super Bowl commercial starring Lil Penny, Anfernee Hardaway’s miniature alter ego. A speed lacing system secures the white leather upper, accented with neon yellow piping and contrasted by purple textile on the padded tongue and collar lining. A jeweled yellow Swoosh adorns the side panel, while Hardaway’s embroidered 1 Cent logo graces the back heel. Anchoring the sneaker is a black Phylon midsole with a visible Max Air unit nestled in the heel.

name: Nike Lunar Roam Platinum Tint Desert Moss
Nike Kobe 8 Protro Radiant Emerald
story: The Nike Kobe 8 Protro ‘Radiant Emerald’ features a white Engineered Mesh upper, covered in an all-over print made up of the jersey numbers that Kobe Bryant wore during his NBA career. An embroidered teal Swoosh adorns the lateral side, while the Mamba’s sheath logo adorns the tongue. The athlete’s signature appears on the lateral heel counter. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a drop-in React foam midsole. Underfoot, a herringbone-traction rubber outsole reveals an exposed carbon fiber shank plate.

name: Nike KD 4 Year of the Dragon 2.0
story: The Nike Zoom KD 4 ‘Year of the Dragon 2.0’ celebrates the Lunar New Year with a khaki-colored upper, built with textile, mesh and seamless synthetic overlays. The low-top is secured with traditional lace closure and an Adaptive Fit strap, accented with a woodgrain pattern and a Noble Red Swoosh. A dragon graphic wraps around the medial Swoosh and extends to the heel, marked with Kevin Durant’s embroidered KD logo. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a Phylon midsole with an encapsulated Zoom Air unit in the forefoot.

Dunk Low GS 'Dance'
story: Made for big kids, the Nike Dunk Low GS ‘Dance’ lives up to its name with a multicolor leather upper with fluid lines that suggest movement. The clashing hues include a crisp white base with contrasting accents in light blue, black, grey, red and pink. The toe box, Swoosh and heel overlay are treated to a reflective finish for enhanced visibility in low-light conditions. A solid black finish is applied to the midsole, built with stitched sidewall construction and supported by a two-tone rubber outsole.

Nike SB Dunk Low Court Purple (2021/2024)
story: The Nike Dunk Low SB ‘Court Purple’ delivers a straightforward colorway of the classic silhouette, redolent of the brand’s pink and silver box eras. The low-top makes use of a white leather upper with contrasting black overlays on the forefoot, eyestay and collar. A heel overlay in Court Purple is matched by the rubber outsole, featuring a grippy traction pattern originally designed for the hardwood. Zoom Air cushioning in the sockliner combines with a stuffed tongue to provide enhanced comfort.
